courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of the course, students are expected to:
1. Demonstrate an understanding of the major concepts of a wide range of approaches to counseling theory and practice;
2. Analyze a case based on theoretical frameworks;
3. Possess an understanding of the techniques employed by different counseling orientations;
4. Identify important counselor attitudes and values that prepare a professional to work with clients with diverse problems and goals; and
5. Gain some initial ideas in constructing a personalized approach to counseling by integrating concepts and techniques from various theoretical orientations.

(Individual course teachers may update the learning outcome as and whenever necessary.)

